# Vulcan - LLM-Powered Demo Generation Platform
# Environment Configuration Template

# =============================================================================
# LLM Configuration (Choose one option)
# =============================================================================

# Option 1: LLM Proxy (OpenAI-compatible, recommended for centralized management)
LLM_PROXY_URL=https://litellm-proxy-service-1059491012611.us-central1.run.app/v1
LLM_PROXY_API_KEY=your-proxy-api-key-here

# Option 2: Direct Anthropic API
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Option 3: Direct OpenAI API
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Optional: Override default models
# Available in proxy: claude-sonnet-4, gpt-4o, gpt-4.1, gpt-3.5-turbo, gemini-2.5-pro, gemini-2.5-flash
# LLM_PROXY_CODE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4
# LLM_PROXY_FAST_MODEL=gpt-3.5-turbo

# =============================================================================
# Elasticsearch Configuration (Required for Query Testing & Data Indexing)
# =============================================================================
# Option 1: Cloud ID + API Key (Recommended for Elastic Cloud)
ELASTICSEARCH_CLOUD_ID=your-deployment-name:base64encodedstring
ELASTICSEARCH_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# Option 2: Direct Endpoint (Alternative)
# ELASTIC_ENDPOINT=https://your-cluster.es.region.cloud.es.io:443
# ELASTIC_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# =============================================================================
# Kibana Configuration (Required for Agent Builder Integration)
# =============================================================================
ELASTICSEARCH_KIBANA_URL=https://your-deployment.kb.region.cloud.es.io:443

# =============================================================================
# Application Configuration (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# DEMO_OUTPUT_DIR=./demos

# =============================================================================
# Notes:
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# 2. Never commit .env to version control
# 3. LLM credentials: Use proxy (Option 1) OR direct API keys (Options 2-3)
# 4. Elasticsearch credentials needed for query testing and data indexing
# 5. Kibana credentials needed for Agent Builder integration
# 
# Priority order for LLM selection:
# - LLM Proxy (if LLM_PROXY_URL and LLM_PROXY_API_KEY are set)
# - Anthropic (if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set)
# - OpenAI (if OPENAI_API_KEY is set)
# - Mock mode (if none are set - for testing only)
